// carries NO community column, and the two edge layers show the two answers to
// "which panel does an edge belong to":
//
// 1. WITHIN (nested, no \`on\`, no cell pick): the compiler derives the layer's
//    partition σ from the declared FK catalog (follows.{src,dst} → members.id →
//    communities). An edge is in a panel only if BOTH endpoints are — the
//    cross-community follow (Farid → Grace) simply is not in either panel's data:
//    14 links, drawn in the panel stroke.
//
// 2. OWNER (top-level, authored first so it draws UNDERNEATH): \`frame: src\` is
//    the declared opt-out of the partition — ALL 15 edges, each assigned to its
//    src node's panel. Only the cross edge peeks out from under layer 1, reaching
//    from the design panel into research (the light stroke).
const communities = db.table('members').groupby(['community'], {});  // distinct communities
